outputs.output_descr:
Taking into account decision 7/CP.17 at COP 17 and the UNFCCC Work Programme on Loss and Damage, and building on the preparatory work done by UNDP as requested by CARICOM Heads of Government and provided through the projects (i) An Overview of Modelling Climate Change Impacts in the Caribbean Region with Contributions from the Pacific Islands and (ii) Quantification and Magnitude of Losses and Damages Resulting from the Impacts of Climate Change: Modelling the transformational impacts and costs of sea level Rise in the Caribbean, this project seeks to continue the support to Caribbean SIDS through the UNFCCC negotiation process, with specific reference to loss and damage as a consequence of slow onset events, UNDP will target its intervention in the following areas:
•	Policy advice on how best to  address loss and damage as a consequence of slow onset events, including assessing and recommending strategies, approaches, options, international mechanisms, to increase resilience and reduce the vulnerability of SIDS, and identifying key programme elements and examining possible financial arrangements for implementing mitigation and adaptation measures;
•	Advocacy and communications on the loss and damage occurring from climate change due to the impact of slow onset events;
•	Capacity building of Caribbean SIDS climate change negotiators to secure commitments in the global climate change negotiations that can increase resilience and reduce vulnerability to climate change impacts.
